</script><div class="caas-body"><p>Michigan Republican Senate candidate John James received campaign contributions&nbsp;and was&nbsp;photographed with the organizer of the rally where conspirators accused of planning to kidnap Michigan Gov. Gretchen Whitmer <a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/10/08/six-men-accused-in-plot-to-kidnap-gov-gretchen-whitmer-after-trump-called-to-liberate-michigan/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:allegedly plotted with a militia to recruit more members" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">allegedly plotted with a militia to recruit more members</a>.</p><p>James, along with Vice President Mike Pence, was photographed with Ryan D. Kelley, a Grand Rapids real estate agent who heads the American Patriot Council, in since-deleted social media images reviewed by Salon. President Donald Trump was also pictured with Kelley in a photo posted to his Facebook profile.</p><figure class="caas-figure"><div class="caas-figure-with-pb" style="max-height: 475.8333333333333px"><div class="caas-img-container caas-img-loader" style="padding-bottom:67%;"><img class="caas-img caas-lazy has-preview" alt="John James; Gretchen Whitmer" src="" data-src="https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/suEPTJe5bLQDU.ZVwR4ohQ--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTcwNTtoPTQ3NS44MzMzMzMzMzMzMzMz/https://s.yimg.com/uu/api/res/1.2/ExgpUmInh.MoetyoKZIRxg--~B/aD0xMTQyO3c9MTY5MjtzbT0xO2FwcGlkPXl0YWNoeW9u/https://media.zenfs.com/en-us/salon_articles_879/ac8dacdd60c7d3781273ef226b4ccc09"><noscript><img alt="John James; Gretchen Whitmer" src="https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/suEPTJe5bLQDU.ZVwR4ohQ--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTcwNTtoPTQ3NS44MzMzMzMzMzMzMzMz/https://s.yimg.com/uu/api/res/1.2/ExgpUmInh.MoetyoKZIRxg--~B/aD0xMTQyO3c9MTY5MjtzbT0xO2FwcGlkPXl0YWNoeW9u/https://media.zenfs.com/en-us/salon_articles_879/ac8dacdd60c7d3781273ef226b4ccc09" class="caas-img"></noscript></div></div><figcaption class="caption-collapse">John James; Gretchen Whitmer</figcaption></figure><p><em>John James and Gretchen Whitmer Photo illustration by Salon/Getty Images</em></p><p>Kelley was the <a href="https://www.americanpatriotcouncil.org/american-patriot-rally-says-well-regulated-militia-rally-to-be-biggest-yet" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:organizer of the &quot;Well-Regulated Militia&quot; rally" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">organizer of the "Well-Regulated Militia" rally</a>&nbsp;at the Michigan capitol in June. The FBI <a href="https://twitter.com/ChadLivengood/status/1314248237683859456" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:alleged in court documents" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">alleged in court documents</a>&nbsp;that the leader of the group who&nbsp;plotted the attack on Whitmer met with militia leader Ty Garbin and a confidential source at the rally to discuss a&nbsp;plan and recruit more members.</p><p>Federal Election Commission records also show that <a href="https://www.opensecrets.org/donor-lookup/results?name=ryan+kelley" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:Kelley has donated thousands" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">Kelley has donated thousands</a>&nbsp;to James' campaign. James, who lost his 2018 Senate bid, is virtually tied with incumbent Sen. Gary Peters, D-Mich., in the latest <a href="https://int.nyt.com/data/documenttools/miwi1020-crosstabs/b0a09cd1cd0048df/full.pdf" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:New York Times/Siena College poll" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">New York Times/Siena College poll</a>.</p><h2>Related Articles</h2><ul class="caas-list caas-list-bullet"><li><p><a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/08/18/this-is-what-collusion-looks-like-gop-led-senate-report-far-more-devastating-than-mueller-probe/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:This is what collusion looks like: GOP-led Senate report far more devastating than Mueller probe" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">This is what collusion looks like: GOP-led Senate report far more devastating than Mueller probe</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/08/03/watchdogs-demand-investigation-into-voter-suppression-tactics-by-trump-donor-running-usps/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:Watchdogs demand investigation into voter suppression tactics by Trump donor running USPS" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">Watchdogs demand investigation into voter suppression tactics by Trump donor running USPS</a></p></li></ul><p>Kelley's pro-gun rally drew "dozens of armed members from various militias, most of them white," to the state capitol where they met with "other fringe groups like Boogaloo Bois and Proud Boys," according to <a href="https://www.bridgemi.com/michigan-government/militias-far-right-groups-recast-selves-mainstream-lansing-gun-rally" among the 13 charged today in the plot to kidnap and possibly kill Governor Whitmer. <a href="https://t.co/KiUeuGUo8O" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:https://t.co/KiUeuGUo8O" href="https://www.salon.com/2020/10/08/six-men-accused-in-plot-to-kidnap-gov-gretchen-whitmer-after-trump-called-to-liberate-michigan/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:alleged that the rally" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">alleged that the rally</a>&nbsp;was among the locations where members plotted to kidnap Whitmer, try her in a remote location in Wisconsin&nbsp;and execute her for "treason" after complaining that the state's coronavirus lockdown had shuttered gyms. The FBI charged 13 men, including members of the <a href="https://www.freep.com/story/news/local/michigan/2020/10/08/whitmer-wolverine-watchmen-militia-michigan/5924617002/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:Wolverine Watchmen militia" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">Wolverine Watchmen militia</a>, in the alleged plot last week.</p><div class="caas-readmore caas-readmore-collapse"><button class="link rapid-noclick-resp caas-button collapse-button" aria-label="" title="" data-ylk="elm:readmore;slk:Story continues">Story continues</button></div><p>Kelley&nbsp;disputed a link between the rally and the plot, noting that one of the suspects was a <a href="https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/news/man-accused-of-hatching-plot-to-kidnap-whitmer-is-blm-supporter-and-made-comments-critical-of-police" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:Black Lives Matter supporter" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">Black Lives Matter supporter</a>&nbsp;and another suspect posted an <a href="https://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/local/michigan/2020/10/09/alleged-kidnapper-posted-anti-trump-video/5940296002/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:anti-Trump video" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">anti-Trump video</a>.</p><p>"The June APC Rally was pro-law enforcement," he said in a statement to Salon.&nbsp;"We coordinated the entire rally with Michigan State Police [and]&nbsp;thanked them publicly for their service.&nbsp;To suggest our rally was a meeting place to discuss a plot against the [governor] is grossly inaccurate."</p><p>James' campaign did not respond to questions from Salon, but it sent over a statement the Republican previously made to reporters.</p><p>"That was insane. That's like the most 2020 headline I've seen this week," <a href="https://wwmt.com/news/local/the-most-2020-headline-john-james-weighs-in-on-alleged-plot-to-kidnap-whitmer" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:he told reporters after the news broke" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">he told reporters after the news broke</a>. "Under no circumstances should we have this at all. I condemn any domestic terrorism, and I hate it in all its forms. I swore an oath to defend the Constitution against all enemies foreign and domestic, and the individuals implicated in this should be prosecuted to the fullest extent."</p><p>"I took an oath to defend the Constitution and this nation against enemies foreign and DOMESTIC," <a href="https://twitter.com/johnjamesmi/status/1314290909568266251?s=21" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:the Army veteran added on Twitter" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">the Army veteran added on Twitter</a>.&nbsp;"Those who threatened our State must be prosecuted to the fullest."</p><p>Trump, who <a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/04/22/coronavirus-apprentice-this-is-what-trump-is-doing-to-us_partner/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:called to &quot;liberate Michigan&quot;" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">called to "liberate Michigan"</a>&nbsp;in April and has been <a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/10/05/stand-back-and-stand-by-new-report-links-trump-to-rise-of-militias-threatening-election-violence/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:accused of emboldening militias" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">accused of emboldening militias</a>, came under fire last month after he <a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/09/30/that-was-a-shtshow-even-fox-news-cant-defend-trump-after-he-refused-to-denounce-white-supremacy/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:refused to denounce" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">refused to denounce</a>&nbsp;the Proud Boys and white supremacists in the first presidential debate. He also <a href="https://www.cnn.com/2020/05/01/politics/donald-trump-michigan-gretchen-whitmer-protests/index.html" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:tweeted in support" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">tweeted in support</a>&nbsp;of protesters who stormed the Michigan capitol, some of whom were armed with guns, to condemn the state's coronavirus restrictions.</p><p>Trump's son Eric <a href="https://www.crainsdetroit.com/retail/whitmer-plot-suspects-past-employment-huron-valley-guns-prompts-trump-campaign-cancel-event" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:scrapped a campaign appearance" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">scrapped a campaign appearance</a>&nbsp;on Monday at a Michigan gun shop where one of the plot suspects previously worked.</p><p>James, who has <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mAQ9Jho1fVY&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;ab_channel=JohnJames" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:billed himself as a unity candidate" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">billed himself as a unity candidate</a>, has also echoed the rhetoric from far-right Michigan groups who have criticized Whitmer's coronavirus restrictions, railing against <a href="https://app.frame.io/presentations/8f7b4169-a069-46c0-86cc-cd3f24472def" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:&quot;socialism&quot;" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">"socialism"</a>&nbsp;and <a href="https://app.frame.io/presentations/db6b1e72-afd3-4ce2-bace-f14caaacb5c8" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:suggesting that Whitmer was dictator" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">suggesting that Whitmer was dictator</a>&nbsp;at recent campaign stops. His campaign stops have <span>drawn members of the Proud Boys</span>, which the FBI has classified as an <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/nov/19/proud-boys-fbi-classification-extremist-group-white-nationalism-report" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:&quot;extremist group with ties to white nationalism.&quot;" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">"extremist group with ties to white nationalism."</a>&nbsp;James has also campaigned with NRA board member Ted Nugent, who has repeatedly <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/1995/05/01/nyregion/chronicle-584995.html" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:espoused support for the militia movement" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">espoused support for the militia movement</a>.</p><p>Whitmer linked Republican rhetoric to the alleged plot against her over the weekend.</p><p>"I do believe that there are still serious threats that groups like this group&nbsp;&nbsp;these domestic terrorists&nbsp;&nbsp;are finding comfort and support in the rhetoric coming out of Republican leadership from the White House to our state House," <a href="https://twitter.com/FaceTheNation/status/1315306872732356609" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:she told CBS News" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">she told CBS News</a>. "And so I remain concerned about safety and integrity going up to this election."</p><p>The American Patriot Council denounced the alleged plot after the FBI announced the arrests.</p><p>"The American Patriot Council in no way condones violence as a form of political action. As the public is well aware, any actions taken by the American Patriot Council have been legal and lawful," <a href="https://www.americanpatriotcouncil.org/press-release-apc-advocates-for-lawful-actions-only" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:the group said in a statement" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">the group said in a statement</a>. "While we hold the view that many public officials are guilty of a litany of crimes, and it has been our goal to hold these officials criminally responsible, we must do so lawfully."</p><p>"The American Patriot Council believes in law and order across the board and that no American citizen should be deprived of their right to due process of law," the statement added. "We have no affiliation with any other groups, nor will we aid or abet anyone using threats or acts of violence. Please take note that we are on the side of law enforcement. To this point, we have not been made aware of any plans of violence, and we believe our members and followers to be patriots."</p><p><br></p><h2>Related Articles</h2><ul class="caas-list caas-list-bullet"><li><p><a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/09/24/democrats-alert-inspector-general-that-gops-biden-probe-directly-implicated-perry-in-corruption/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:Democrats alert inspector general that GOP's Biden probe directly implicated Perry in corruption" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">Democrats alert inspector general that GOP's Biden probe directly implicated Perry in corruption</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/09/25/insult-to-every-family-trump-unveils-bogus-health-care-plan-that-doesnt-actually-do-anything/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:Insult to every family: Trump unveils bogus health care &quot;plan&quot; that doesn't actually do anything" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">Insult to every family: Trump unveils bogus health care "plan" that doesn't actually do anything</a></p></li></ul><p><br></p><p>Trump, meanwhile, <a href="https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2020/10/08/trump-slams-gretchen-whitmer-not-saying-thank-you-she-did/5932028002/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:attacked Whitmer" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">attacked Whitmer</a>&nbsp;over the coronavirus restrictions after the arrests were announced. </script><div class="caas-body"><p>Michigan Republican Senate candidate John James received campaign contributions&nbsp;and was&nbsp;photographed with the organizer of the rally where conspirators accused of planning to kidnap Michigan Gov. Gretchen Whitmer <a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/10/08/six-men-accused-in-plot-to-kidnap-gov-gretchen-whitmer-after-trump-called-to-liberate-michigan/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:allegedly plotted with a militia to recruit more members" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">allegedly plotted with a militia to recruit more members</a>.</p><p>James, along with Vice President Mike Pence, was photographed with Ryan D. Kelley, a Grand Rapids real estate agent who heads the American Patriot Council, in since-deleted social media images reviewed by Salon. President Donald Trump was also pictured with Kelley in a photo posted to his Facebook profile.</p><figure class="caas-figure"><div class="caas-figure-with-pb" style="max-height: 475.8333333333333px"><div class="caas-img-container caas-img-loader" style="padding-bottom:67%;"><img class="caas-img caas-lazy has-preview" alt="John James; Gretchen Whitmer" src="" data-src="https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/suEPTJe5bLQDU.ZVwR4ohQ--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTcwNTtoPTQ3NS44MzMzMzMzMzMzMzMz/https://s.yimg.com/uu/api/res/1.2/ExgpUmInh.MoetyoKZIRxg--~B/aD0xMTQyO3c9MTY5MjtzbT0xO2FwcGlkPXl0YWNoeW9u/https://media.zenfs.com/en-us/salon_articles_879/ac8dacdd60c7d3781273ef226b4ccc09"><noscript><img alt="John James; Gretchen Whitmer" src="https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/suEPTJe5bLQDU.ZVwR4ohQ--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTcwNTtoPTQ3NS44MzMzMzMzMzMzMzMz/https://s.yimg.com/uu/api/res/1.2/ExgpUmInh.MoetyoKZIRxg--~B/aD0xMTQyO3c9MTY5MjtzbT0xO2FwcGlkPXl0YWNoeW9u/https://media.zenfs.com/en-us/salon_articles_879/ac8dacdd60c7d3781273ef226b4ccc09" class="caas-img"></noscript></div></div><figcaption class="caption-collapse">John James; Gretchen Whitmer</figcaption></figure><p><em>John James and Gretchen Whitmer Photo illustration by Salon/Getty Images</em></p><p>Kelley was the <a href="https://www.americanpatriotcouncil.org/american-patriot-rally-says-well-regulated-militia-rally-to-be-biggest-yet" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:organizer of the &quot;Well-Regulated Militia&quot; rally" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">organizer of the "Well-Regulated Militia" rally</a>&nbsp;at the Michigan capitol in June. The FBI <a href="https://twitter.com/ChadLivengood/status/1314248237683859456" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:alleged in court documents" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">alleged in court documents</a>&nbsp;that the leader of the group who&nbsp;plotted the attack on Whitmer met with militia leader Ty Garbin and a confidential source at the rally to discuss a&nbsp;plan and recruit more members.</p><p>Federal Election Commission records also show that <a href="https://www.opensecrets.org/donor-lookup/results?name=ryan+kelley" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:Kelley has donated thousands" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">Kelley has donated thousands</a>&nbsp;to James' campaign. James, who lost his 2018 Senate bid, is virtually tied with incumbent Sen. Gary Peters, D-Mich., in the latest <a href="https://int.nyt.com/data/documenttools/miwi1020-crosstabs/b0a09cd1cd0048df/full.pdf" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:New York Times/Siena College poll" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">New York Times/Siena College poll</a>.</p><h2>Related Articles</h2><ul class="caas-list caas-list-bullet"><li><p><a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/08/18/this-is-what-collusion-looks-like-gop-led-senate-report-far-more-devastating-than-mueller-probe/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:This is what collusion looks like: GOP-led Senate report far more devastating than Mueller probe" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">This is what collusion looks like: GOP-led Senate report far more devastating than Mueller probe</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/08/03/watchdogs-demand-investigation-into-voter-suppression-tactics-by-trump-donor-running-usps/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:Watchdogs demand investigation into voter suppression tactics by Trump donor running USPS" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">Watchdogs demand investigation into voter suppression tactics by Trump donor running USPS</a></p></li></ul><p>Kelley's pro-gun rally drew "dozens of armed members from various militias, most of them white," to the state capitol where they met with "other fringe groups like Boogaloo Bois and Proud Boys," according to <a href="https://www.bridgemi.com/michigan-government/militias-far-right-groups-recast-selves-mainstream-lansing-gun-rally" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:Bridge Michigan" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">Bridge Michigan</a>.</p><div class="twitter-tweet-wrapper"><blockquote placeholder data-theme="light" class="twitter-tweet"><div class="caas-card-loader small fixed-height"></div><p>Spokesperson for <a href="https://twitter.com/MIAttyGen?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:@MIAttyGen" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">@MIAttyGen</a> confirms these two men -- seen here, armed in the Michigan Senate gallery during session on April 30 -- were among the 13 charged today in the plot to kidnap and possibly kill Governor Whitmer. <a href="https://t.co/KiUeuGUo8O" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:https://t.co/KiUeuGUo8O" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">https://t.co/KiUeuGUo8O</a></p><p> Zach Gorchow (@ZachGorchow) <a href="https://twitter.com/ZachGorchow/status/1314330815250259977?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:October 8, 2020" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">October 8, 2020</a></p></blockquote></div><p>The FBI <a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/10/08/six-men-accused-in-plot-to-kidnap-gov-gretchen-whitmer-after-trump-called-to-liberate-michigan/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:alleged that the rally" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">alleged that the rally</a>&nbsp;was among the locations where members plotted to kidnap Whitmer, try her in a remote location in Wisconsin&nbsp;and execute her for "treason" after complaining that the state's coronavirus lockdown had shuttered gyms. The FBI charged 13 men, including members of the <a href="https://www.freep.com/story/news/local/michigan/2020/10/08/whitmer-wolverine-watchmen-militia-michigan/5924617002/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:Wolverine Watchmen militia" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">Wolverine Watchmen militia</a>, in the alleged plot last week.</p><div class="caas-readmore caas-readmore-collapse"><button class="link rapid-noclick-resp caas-button collapse-button" aria-label="" title="" data-ylk="elm:readmore;slk:Story continues">Story continues</button></div><p>Kelley&nbsp;disputed a link between the rally and the plot, noting that one of the suspects was a <a href="https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/news/man-accused-of-hatching-plot-to-kidnap-whitmer-is-blm-supporter-and-made-comments-critical-of-police" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:Black Lives Matter supporter" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">Black Lives Matter supporter</a>&nbsp;and another suspect posted an <a href="https://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/local/michigan/2020/10/09/alleged-kidnapper-posted-anti-trump-video/5940296002/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:anti-Trump video" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">anti-Trump video</a>.</p><p>"The June APC Rally was pro-law enforcement," he said in a statement to Salon.&nbsp;"We coordinated the entire rally with Michigan State Police [and]&nbsp;thanked them publicly for their service.&nbsp;To suggest our rally was a meeting place to discuss a plot against the [governor] is grossly inaccurate."</p><p>James' campaign did not respond to questions from Salon, but it sent over a statement the Republican previously made to reporters.</p><p>"That was insane. That's like the most 2020 headline I've seen this week," <a href="https://wwmt.com/news/local/the-most-2020-headline-john-james-weighs-in-on-alleged-plot-to-kidnap-whitmer" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:he told reporters after the news broke" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">he told reporters after the news broke</a>. "Under no circumstances should we have this at all. I condemn any domestic terrorism, and I hate it in all its forms. I swore an oath to defend the Constitution against all enemies foreign and domestic, and the individuals implicated in this should be prosecuted to the fullest extent."</p><p>"I took an oath to defend the Constitution and this nation against enemies foreign and DOMESTIC," <a href="https://twitter.com/johnjamesmi/status/1314290909568266251?s=21" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:the Army veteran added on Twitter" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">the Army veteran added on Twitter</a>.&nbsp;"Those who threatened our State must be prosecuted to the fullest."</p><p>Trump, who <a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/04/22/coronavirus-apprentice-this-is-what-trump-is-doing-to-us_partner/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:called to &quot;liberate Michigan&quot;" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">called to "liberate Michigan"</a>&nbsp;in April and has been <a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/10/05/stand-back-and-stand-by-new-report-links-trump-to-rise-of-militias-threatening-election-violence/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:accused of emboldening militias" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">accused of emboldening militias</a>, came under fire last month after he <a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/09/30/that-was-a-shtshow-even-fox-news-cant-defend-trump-after-he-refused-to-denounce-white-supremacy/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:refused to denounce" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">refused to denounce</a>&nbsp;the Proud Boys and white supremacists in the first presidential debate. He also <a href="https://www.cnn.com/2020/05/01/politics/donald-trump-michigan-gretchen-whitmer-protests/index.html" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:tweeted in support" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">tweeted in support</a>&nbsp;of protesters who stormed the Michigan capitol, some of whom were armed with guns, to condemn the state's coronavirus restrictions.</p><p>Trump's son Eric <a href="https://www.crainsdetroit.com/retail/whitmer-plot-suspects-past-employment-huron-valley-guns-prompts-trump-campaign-cancel-event" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:scrapped a campaign appearance" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">scrapped a campaign appearance</a>&nbsp;on Monday at a Michigan gun shop where one of the plot suspects previously worked.</p><p>James, who has <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mAQ9Jho1fVY&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;ab_channel=JohnJames" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:billed himself as a unity candidate" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">billed himself as a unity candidate</a>, has also echoed the rhetoric from far-right Michigan groups who have criticized Whitmer's coronavirus restrictions, railing against <a href="https://app.frame.io/presentations/8f7b4169-a069-46c0-86cc-cd3f24472def" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:&quot;socialism&quot;" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">"socialism"</a>&nbsp;and <a href="https://app.frame.io/presentations/db6b1e72-afd3-4ce2-bace-f14caaacb5c8" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:suggesting that Whitmer was dictator" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">suggesting that Whitmer was dictator</a>&nbsp;at recent campaign stops. His campaign stops have <span>drawn members of the Proud Boys</span>, which the FBI has classified as an <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/nov/19/proud-boys-fbi-classification-extremist-group-white-nationalism-report" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:&quot;extremist group with ties to white nationalism.&quot;" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">"extremist group with ties to white nationalism."</a>&nbsp;James has also campaigned with NRA board member Ted Nugent, who has repeatedly <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/1995/05/01/nyregion/chronicle-584995.html" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:espoused support for the militia movement" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">espoused support for the militia movement</a>.</p><p>Whitmer linked Republican rhetoric to the alleged plot against her over the weekend.</p><p>"I do believe that there are still serious threats that groups like this group&nbsp;&nbsp;these domestic terrorists&nbsp;&nbsp;are finding comfort and support in the rhetoric coming out of Republican leadership from the White House to our state House," <a href="https://twitter.com/FaceTheNation/status/1315306872732356609" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:she told CBS News" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">she told CBS News</a>. "And so I remain concerned about safety and integrity going up to this election."</p><p>The American Patriot Council denounced the alleged plot after the FBI announced the arrests.</p><p>"The American Patriot Council in no way condones violence as a form of political action. As the public is well aware, any actions taken by the American Patriot Council have been legal and lawful," <a href="https://www.americanpatriotcouncil.org/press-release-apc-advocates-for-lawful-actions-only" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:the group said in a statement" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">the group said in a statement</a>. "While we hold the view that many public officials are guilty of a litany of crimes, and it has been our goal to hold these officials criminally responsible, we must do so lawfully."</p><p>"The American Patriot Council believes in law and order across the board and that no American citizen should be deprived of their right to due process of law," the statement added. "We have no affiliation with any other groups, nor will we aid or abet anyone using threats or acts of violence. Please take note that we are on the side of law enforcement. To this point, we have not been made aware of any plans of violence, and we believe our members and followers to be patriots."</p><p><br></p><h2>Related Articles</h2><ul class="caas-list caas-list-bullet"><li><p><a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/09/24/democrats-alert-inspector-general-that-gops-biden-probe-directly-implicated-perry-in-corruption/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:Democrats alert inspector general that GOP's Biden probe directly implicated Perry in corruption" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">Democrats alert inspector general that GOP's Biden probe directly implicated Perry in corruption</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.salon.com/2020/09/25/insult-to-every-family-trump-unveils-bogus-health-care-plan-that-doesnt-actually-do-anything/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:Insult to every family: Trump unveils bogus health care &quot;plan&quot; that doesn't actually do anything" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">Insult to every family: Trump unveils bogus health care "plan" that doesn't actually do anything</a></p></li></ul><p><br></p><p>Trump, meanwhile, <a href="https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2020/10/08/trump-slams-gretchen-whitmer-not-saying-thank-you-she-did/5932028002/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" data-ylk="slk:attacked Whitmer" class="link rapid-noclick-resp">attacked Whitmer</a>&nbsp;over the coronavirus restrictions after the arrests were announced.
